  "text": "Knee flexion increases as the angle of side-cutting increases. [CITATION_1] Increased knee flexion has been linked to increased ACL protection. This implies that at increased side-cut angles, the ACL is better protected through a natural response to increased knee flexion. No published studies have been performed assessing sex differences in knee flexion during a rapid change-of-direction maneuver !90",
